com.appboy.ui.inappmessage.listeners

Interface IHtmlInAppMessageActionListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AppboyDefaultHtmlInAppMessageActionListener

    public interface IHtmlInAppMessageActionListener
    The IHtmlInAppMessageActionListener allows for the overriding of the default Braze display handling and setting custom behavior during the display of Html In-App Messages.

      • onNewsfeedClicked

        boolean onNewsfeedClicked(IInAppMessage inAppMessage,
                          java.lang.String url,
                          android.os.Bundle queryBundle)
        Parameters:
        inAppMessage - the In-App Message being displayed.
        url - the url clicked.
        queryBundle - a bundle of the query part of the url.
        Returns:
        boolean flag to indicate to Braze whether the click has been manually handled. If true, Braze will log a click and do nothing. If false, Braze will also navigate to the Newsfeed.

      • onCustomEventFired

        boolean onCustomEventFired(IInAppMessage inAppMessage,
                           java.lang.String url,
                           android.os.Bundle queryBundle)
        Parameters:
        inAppMessage - the In-App Message being displayed.
        url - the url clicked.
        queryBundle - a bundle of the query part of the url.
        Returns:
        boolean flag to indicate to Braze whether the click has been manually handled. If true, Braze will do nothing. If false, Braze will log the custom event.

      • onOtherUrlAction

        boolean onOtherUrlAction(IInAppMessage inAppMessage,
                         java.lang.String url,
                         android.os.Bundle queryBundle)
        Parameters:
        inAppMessage - the In-App Message being displayed.
        url - the url clicked.
        queryBundle - a bundle of the query part of the url.
        Returns:
        boolean flag to indicate to Braze whether the click has been manually handled. If true, Braze will log a click and do nothing. If false, Braze will also handle the URL.
